cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel attention mechanism for visual question answering, which involves both computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
